    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-01-18T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-01-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="638"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/852: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-01-18T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >January 18, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 18—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Department’s 9, January 16, 5 p.m. Clive made oral and written representations
                    today as outlined in Department’s telegram. Arita<note n="8" xml:id="d638fn8">K.
                        Arita, Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> replied that the
                    Japanese Navy is opposed to accepting a qualitative without a quantitative limit
                    but that he would investigate and would <pb facs="0633" n="621" xml:id="pg_621"
                    /> try to give a reply “in a week or a little more”. Clive pressed him for a
                    more urgent reply. He has promised to inform me as soon as the reply is
                    received.</p>
                <p>Clive says that both the British and German Naval Attachés believe that the
                    Japanese naval authorities are now considering the construction of battleships
                    of 50,000 tons with 18-inch guns.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
